Algorithm 1 Upward-Downward Variational Inference
Input: Observed data $X = \{X_n\}.
Output: Global parameters of the Generlized GBN $W^{(l:L)}$.
Set mini-batch size $m$ and the number of layer $L$
Initialize the parameters $W^{(l:L)}$;
for iter = 1,2,... do
1. Randomly select a mini-batch of $m$ documents to form a subset $X = \{x_i\}_{i=1,m}$;
2. Infer the variational posterior for gamma latent variable $\{\Theta_i^{(l)}\}_{i=1,m}^{L-1}$ with the inference network via Eq. (9) ;
3. Drawn random noise $\{\epsilon_i^{(l)}\}_{i=1,m}^{L-1}$ from a uniform distribution;
4. Sample hierarchical latent variables $\{\Theta_i^{(l)}\}_{i=1,m}^{L-1}$ from Weibull distribution with $\{\epsilon_i^{(l)}\}_{i=1,m}^{L-1}$ via Eq. (7);
5. Calculate $V_{\mathbf{W}^{(1:1)}} \mathcal{L} \left(\mathbf{W}^{(1: L)} ; \mathbf{X} ;\left\{\epsilon_i^{(l)}\right\}_{i=1,m}^{L-1}\right)$ according to Eq. (11), and update encoder parameters and decoder parameters $\mathbf{W}^{(l: L)}$ jointly ;
end for
